        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Exertional syncope in a patient with aortic stenosis is a classic presentation of cardiac syncope from structural heart disease. The fixed obstruction prevents adequate cardiac output augmentation during exercise, causing cerebral hypoperfusion. This is a high-risk presentation requiring urgent evaluation for valve replacement (SAVR or TAVR)."
